                    <msContents>
                        <summary>The rulings of the Raash (Asher ben Yehiel)</summary>
                        <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Arch_Selden_A_53_a">
                            <locus>ff. 1r-160v</locus>
                            <author ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/301582237" key="person_301582237">
                                <persName>Jacob ben Asher, approximately 1269-approximately 1340   </persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="he">יעקב בן אשר</persName>
                            </author>
                            <title xml:lang="he">קצור פסקי הרא"ש</title>
                            <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ḳitsur pisḳe ha-Raʼash</title>
                            <note>Ends with Nedarim.</note>
                            <note>Marginal notes containing omissions and extracts from the Mordekhai and <foreign xml:lang="he">נ"ר</foreign>.</note>
                            <note>At the beginning of the MS, there is a letter of Mordekhai ben Shabbtai <foreign xml:lang="he">מימורת</foreign> to R. Shlomoh Agul, dated 14 Iyar 5336 (1576 CE).</note>
                            <note>At the end, a note extracted from <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495" key="person_100185495">Maimonides</persName>' commentary on the Mishnah.</note>
                            <textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>
